column3:
“This strain smells like fresh citrusy lemons growing in a rain forest. Once it's ground, it smells like a blast of tropical citrus that tinges the nostrils. It was so enticing that I literally accidentally snorted a little bit because I couldn't get enough of the smell.
When you smoke it it tastes Mother Earth put her dick in a rain forest. And the high has me high enough that I just wrote that. Head feels nice and c...”
“This strain is currently one of my go-to" sativas.  It's always a great high for when I want to have a nice quiet night at home meditating
column4: but I've also used it during small gatherings and I've noticed it can make me pretty chatty.”"

column3: “Hempstar is my new favorite sativa it woke me up and kept me up really euphoric, it also gave me the giggles and i had a mad munchie run, i would only use this strain in the morning, never at night. im giving this strain a 5 out of 5. one of my top strains forsure .”

“this is the kind of bud you want to pull out when you are going to be smoking a bunch with the boys. great hits, smooth from beginning to end and a classic sativa. when trying for the first time you probably want to get a quarter ;)”
“My favorite strain.  Always covered in THC trichomes, powdered all over the delicious buds.  Pure cannabis happiness and energy in this green--almost yellow from THC--plant .”

“Hempstar produces very nice looking buds.  Mine are light green with mischievous orange hairs everywhere.  An inviting frosty layer coats the whole nug.  Pungent earthy tones are what I'm getting and there's an underlying scent I can't put my finger on...it's an herbal almost basil-ish smell.

The bust is mediocre but the vapour is thick and smooth giving an earthy taste.

The effects are nice and strong and motivate...”
“Lots of crystals, nice nugs,crazy high, keif is godlike.”

“Really good sativa
Very euphoric and creative and imaginative.
I just imagined a month of 5 realities in my mind during my walk to star trek beyond. 
Let's see how the movie ends up”

“Really good sativa
Very euphoric and creative and imaginative.
I just imagined a month of 5 realities in my mind during my walk to star trek beyond. 
Let's see how the movie ends up”

“I enjoy this sativa strain for its relaxing and uplifting high.  This is a wonderful strain to start your day with, as its energetic but sitll relaxing enough to lower anxiety or fears. The taste is earthy and woody with a spicy undertone. I suggest this to anyone who has those first day of work gitters and just needs a boost to get them going and confident for the day.”

“So far, Hempstar is my favorite sativa strain to-date. Not only do I work with startups, but I freelance on the side; so you can imagine the hours I have to work sometimes.

This strain seems to be the perfect sativa for dialing in my focus and getting in the flow of my work. It's also been great for those walks where you want to brainstorm some new idea. 

Highly recommend it for people that want something to help f...”

“Hempstar is a strain that definitely lives up to being a sativa. As soon as I smoked it I felt relaxed and calm, my head was completely clear and gave me the energy to get on with my day. It made me very mellow but still very functional and aware. It's a great strain to start your day.”
“Lots of crystals, nice nugs,crazy high, keif is godlike.”
“by far the best cannabis I've had. huge, thick, hairy trichrome covered buds that smell and smoke great”

“Being a English student, this is my go-to weed. My creativity aided by Hempstar allows me to have confidence and makes my work unique. This usually helps me to get the highest grades in class and got me 95% in my first year.”

“Try it.. It'll be one of your go to sativa strains for sure.. Great taste and smell, perfect combo of pine and sweet/fruityness. High is not overwhelming but strong, and it definitely had the biggest buds I've seen since I started ordering online. Given it's parents are haze and northern lights it's no wonder it has such strong characteristics.”
“It thunderfucked me in the braiiiiin”

“Awesome for getting energized and getting stuff done around the house. 3 hours later the house, yard and garage are in tip-top shape. My heart was beating noticeably faster after vaping 0.5 grams. Taste and smell were very subtle. Gentle come down. This is a top 5 strain for me.”

“Tried this strain for the first time. Used my new Pax2. Felt only a gentle high. Not like the sativas I've been trying since getting my card. Thought I'd give it a shot the old fashion way by rolling in a dube many hours later that day and again gentle high... 
But I did get my period this afternoon and I've been getting harsh cramps the past few months but no cramps at all today. So I'll give it a couple stars for i...”
“Very intense, good uplifting/social high. Very skunky flowers, the most pungent strain i have had by far.”

“Try it.. It'll be one of your go to sativa strains for sure.. Great taste and smell, perfect combo of pine and sweet/fruityness. High is not overwhelming but strong, and it definitely had the biggest buds I've seen since I started ordering online. Given it's parents are haze and northern lights it's no wonder it has such strong characteristics.”

“Being a English student, this is my go-to weed. My creativity aided by Hempstar allows me to have confidence and makes my work unique. This usually helps me to get the highest grades in class and got me 95% in my first year.”

“Some good daytime bud. Very, very dense. Very hard buds. Still easy to bust up in a hand grinder. Covered in crystals, too. The smell is that classic hempstar smell. I can't really describe it. Woody smelling. But a sweet wood smell. If that makes sense. The high is a really clear, energetic buzz. Something to smoke right in the morning to take away any pain, nausea or downright crappy feelings.”
“Nice for productivity.  I have a high tolerance though and found it wore off very quickly.”
“I loved Hempstar! It made me feel so uplifted and active. Anyone and everyone should and must try this strain if they are feeling down or just want to get the motivation to do something!”
“Very intense, good uplifting/social high. Very skunky flowers, the most pungent strain i have had by far.”
“looooove this strain. such an old skool strain that you don't see much anymore. but the same as the good old days of the 80s/90s.”
“good day time strain - keeps you up and focused, not too hungry and generally very pleasant while doing daily chores.. i like it on the weekend with a pint”

“Awesome for getting energized and getting stuff done around the house. 3 hours later the house, yard and garage are in tip-top shape. My heart was beating noticeably faster after vaping 0.5 grams. Taste and smell were very subtle. Gentle come down. This is a top 5 strain for me.”

“Nice strain, good mental buzz. Not to use if you want to work on a project or write something. More a social buzz. You wanna chat with peoples. On the taste side sweet and earthy is a good description. Not the best in term of taste.”

“Its a mellow type of sativa high, it almost feels like a hybrid type feeling but still much more towards the sativa.  Its definitely towards the more laid back kind of thing, its not nearly as energetic as something like Trainwreck. Still a great taste and the smoke of the stock I have is very smooth.”
“nice taste nice buzz”

“really good day time smoker that still got me nice and tired at the end of the day. for whatever reason, I built up tolerance for this strain faster than usually and found in hard to get blazed for the rest of the bag.”

“My favourite daytime strain to get stuff done. It's a very uplifting high, but not overwhelming.  It makes me energetic, happy, yet focused and driven. Made cleaning my house a pleasant and enjoyable chore.

It hits quickly, and last a decent time. Found it a bit harsh but only used a old school metal pipe. Generic taste and smell. 

It can make me slighlty anxious if I smoke too much, but I prefer to stay at a low t...”

“Ok
This is my second time smoking hempstar, and i believe i have travelled to japan for dinner just now.
Damn”

“this is a very nice strain. i just had a nice wake and bake with my boyfriend out of our new bong and it was defiantly a nice way to start my morning. it wakes you up and it hit me pretty quickly. it’s been a few minutes since i’ve smoked it and the effects of it being sativa are very obvious. it is a little harsh and has a peppery taste to it. i found that smoking it out of the bong or smoking it in a blunt makes it...”
“Smooth, cerebral, relaxing, pasties, good focus and attention, creative, soothing, potent.”
“Always been one of my top shelfs. Very blingy buds! Found the high to be very strong cerebral effect. Almost was seeing black specs upon exhale! Massive dense buds,”

“From a dealers perspective, this strain sells super easy to the people looking to get a really clean crisp energetic sativa high. High quality high but you need to smoke a bowl more than usual to get it”
“Heavy relaxation and stress relief.  Feeling creative and spacey.”
“Awesome sativa with a giggly, fun, creative high. Beware dry eyes aside from the usual dry mouth.”
“Great energizing strain for daytime use. Incredible flavour and covered in thrichomes. Very well balanced strain. Good for nausea, headaches, energy and pain relief.”
“1# Sativa Strain To Try With Friends and To Brighten Your Day. This Strain Delivers Very Uplifting Effects And the taste is quick tasty”
“Slightly herbal with a hint of citrus. Uplifting and energizing strain and it works well with improving my mood”
“Really good sativa, takes a little while to hit you but a great feeling when it does!”

“One of the funnest strains that I've tried. Really uplifting, fun and an awesome tingling sensation/increased senses all over the body. I love doing a little bit of this before skiing to get inspired, reduce nerves and pain.”

“Good strain... Makes me feel focused, energetic and very creative... I recommend for those days that you don't want to get out of bed but there is a lot of important things to do... One of my favorites.”
“thank you.”

“Creeper. One moment I was wondering where the buzz was, and the next moment, shazam!
The taste is nothing special but the high lasted a while.”

“Super pungent when grown proper good skunky  flavour this strain is mad stinky I love it good for hiking cause u don't get munchies can give u anxiety if u puff it for a long time so it's just a casual smoke come dressed in crystals with chunky structure and fat leafs a beautiful plant indeed two thumb up !!!”

“This strain was incredibly popular at the compassion club when I first started using cannabis, and as a result I ended up using it a lot. Honestly though, while it got the job done, I found it made me too anxious and paranoid to use it long-term or at night. I have a pre-existing anxiety condition, so others might not react the same, but for me it was too stimulating.”
“I really like the sativa effect of this one. Slight peppery spice terpene profile from the haze also adds the excellent mind shift and mildly psychedelic effects.”

“Such a great strain. It gives me a chill high, but makes me chatty. It has some trippy effects visually at times , but no paranoia or anxiety when smoking this strain. I find some satvias can make me a bit anxious at times but not with this strain. 

One of the best highs I've had in awhile.”

“YEeeea boys the shit is fire.

Taste is yum, im blazed, amen”

“Have tried this strain many times and always get reminded with the first joint, how potent it is. Great high, pretty giggly, and a great motivator weed. Two thumbs up! Will definitely buy this again.”

“The best Sativa I have ever tried, hands down.  Powerful as heck, and classic Sativa superlatives x 10 000.  The best I've ever tried personally, obviously different crops from different places will be unique, but this one I got right now... WHOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOweeeeee damn son.  I've never been this high in my life the last 3 days.
Then later on I introduce some more indica type shit, right now Black Diamond and Water...”
“HempStar is amazing. Very energetic and creative bud. As an artist, this one lets me be very focused, happy and confident in my work.”

“This strain is extremely pungent! A very nice body high that allows you to feel your body pain and sores dissolve away in the comfort of your own space. Euphoric and uplifted yet relaxed at the same time. Great strain!”
“Smooth, cerebral, relaxing, pasties, good focus and attention, creative, soothing, potent.”
“one of my favourite sativas - awake, analytical, giggily, creative, focused, lasts for hours. not anxious or paranoid but huge case of the munchies every time!”
“Longtime Favorite. Chatty, giggly, great for movies. BAD for munchies”

“this is a very nice strain. i just had a nice wake and bake with my boyfriend out of our new bong and it was defiantly a nice way to start my morning. it wakes you up and it hit me pretty quickly. it’s been a few minutes since i’ve smoked it and the effects of it being sativa are very obvious. it is a little harsh and has a peppery taste to it. i found that smoking it out of the bong or smoking it in a blunt makes it...”

“My favourite daytime strain to get stuff done. It's a very uplifting high, but not overwhelming.  It makes me energetic, happy, yet focused and driven. Made cleaning my house a pleasant and enjoyable chore.

It hits quickly, and last a decent time. Found it a bit harsh but only used a old school metal pipe. Generic taste and smell. 

It can make me slighlty anxious if I smoke too much, but I prefer to stay at a low t...”
“very earthy really mello and no after taste, Really good as budder too.”

“Fantastic woodsy taste. Clear headed euphoria without the sluggishness. Also perfect for people who have IBS related nausea (which I do) getting their appetite back! Actually enjoyed my dinner tonight after some Hempstar.

I didn't use much (a pinch, vaped) but I can feel the potential for use with music and creative work! Definitely a good daytime medicine., for wanting to get things done, and de-stressing.”

“Known for its big leaves and epic look Hemp* is awesome if u want super stinky gooey chunky nugs this is a great one it can give u anxiety if u smoke to much it actually suppresses hunger good for ppl who don't want to get the munchies”

“oooooboooyyyyyooooboooooyyyy

pretty blessed, id say at least a quality dank”
“Heavy relaxation and stress relief.  Feeling creative and spacey.”

“From a dealers perspective, this strain sells super easy to the people looking to get a really clean crisp energetic sativa high. High quality high but you need to smoke a bowl more than usual to get it”
“Always been one of my top shelfs. Very blingy buds! Found the high to be very strong cerebral effect. Almost was seeing black specs upon exhale! Massive dense buds,”

“Ok
This is my second time smoking hempstar, and i believe i have travelled to japan for dinner just now.
Damn”

“really good day time smoker that still got me nice and tired at the end of the day. for whatever reason, I built up tolerance for this strain faster than usually and found in hard to get blazed for the rest of the bag.”
“nice taste nice buzz”
“great for recreational use.Definitely leaves a dizzy and very active brain waves.”
“Uplifting, energizing, light sativa with creative talkative mood. High is not very strong. Mild herbal taste.”
“Great tasting, easy smoking flower. Full body relief, while remaining focused and alert. Very happy with this choice!”

“Most of the time this strain taste like sweat skunky grass but not in a good way, just too generic and has no real medical properties. just a over hyped  strain for no good reason, I would not recommend it.”
“It's been some time since I've had this chronic strain on my bowl. And the fact that I remember this strain and it's properties, I would say it's a must try smoke!”
“heavy hitting classic sativa for me.. one of my first strains”
“Good sativa, wasn't to fond of the smell or taste. It's a uplifting focus high. I would purchase again.”
“Reminds me of  red hair " from the "80's " as far as smell and taste..I like it will forsure buy again.”"
“Hempstar is an awesome strain for listening to music or going for a nature walk - it induces a very introspective high that lasts a decent while and the comedown is quite calm. 3.5/5”
“Nice and heady and makes shitty work fun! Actually gives you energy but you don't realize because you're baked!”

“Defintely the best strain I have ever had. Such an amazing euphoric an happy high, perfect for daytime, I just wanted to go and get things done. Made it kind of weird when I was having a shower and doing cleaning and chores at 2am :P”

“Okay. So I invited a girl over to have some of this with me...it works on girls let me tell you! hahaha gets them motivated" so to say. the only thing wrong with it was that she didn't get to high because she couldn't hit the pipe properly. one thing I did notice is that the effects of this strain don't last as long as the effects of let's say chocolope or maybe purple voodoo. but with a little higher dose I would r...”"

“I really enjoyed this strain. It had an upbeat feel to it & the high lasted a while for me. I like to watch movies when I'm baked & usually when I watch movies high, I zone out or fall asleep through the opening credits. With Hempstar, I felt incredibly focused & every word stuck with me. On a separate occasion, it made me rather energetic. Both times, however, I felt really happy & destressed. One solid sativa.”
“One of my favourite sativas. Powerful stuff so take it slow when smoking :) smoke one bowl and clean the entire house.”
“gives me the perfect high. mellow, relaxed, happy. No negatives”
“great smooth flavour, dense & dry buds, great uplifting high”
“Nice destresser and excellent high to relax you for the night being! Very uplifting”
“Very nice and clean. helped me a lot with nausea,  without leaving me tired and useless.”

“- Subtle citrus taste
- Head high
- Blurry vision
- Awake, yet chinky eyes”
“I loved this strain! Smoked like 10 bowls in one session. I was completely gone. Probably the highest i have ever been. Used a gravity bong for it though.”
“wasn't my favorite sativa ever. made me cough excessively, with a high that wasn't worth the pain. however, it tastes sweet and earthy and smells citrusy.”
